    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Phyllanthus niruri are diabetes, and hepatitis, with studies showing it lowers blood sugar levels and reduces liver inflammation, kidney stones, and gallstones, by preventing the formation of stone-forming substances, hypertension, by reducing blood pressure and improving cardiovascular health, cancer, particularly hepatoma, by inhibiting the growth of cancer cells, and inflammation, which is linked to many diseases. Phyllanthus niruri also shows potential in treating hepatitis B, gastritis, and inflammatory bowel disease by reducing the severity of symptoms and preventing complications. Additionally, it has been found to prevent cancer, by reducing the risk of tumor formation, and atherosclerosis, by reducing the buildup of plaque in arteries, jaundice, by reducing bilirubin levels, eczema, by reducing inflammation and promoting skin health, osteoporosis, by reducing bone resorption, fever, by reducing body temperature, and rheumatoid arthritis, and gout, by reducing joint inflammation. Furthermore, it has been found to inhibit the growth of cancer cells in cancer, and to reduce the severity of symptoms in asthma, and hepatoma. Phyllanthus niruri has also been found to reduce the risk of cancer prevention and to reduce the severity of symptoms in atherosclerosis.",
