    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Phyllanthus niruri are phyllanthin, a lignan with hepatoprotective properties that has been shown to inhibit lipid peroxidation and oxidative stress, quercetin, a flavonoid with potent anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects that has been demonstrated to inhibit COX-2 and iNOS enzymes, flavonoids, which possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, phenolic acids, including caffeic and ferulic acids, that exhibit antimicrobial and antioxidant properties, and kaempferol, a flavonoid with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects that has been found to inhibit TNF-alpha production and NF-kappa B activation. These constituents work synergistically to confer the plant's therapeutic benefits, including its antiviral, anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and hepatoprotective properties. Studies have shown that phyllanthin and quercetin are responsible for the plant's antiviral and anti-inflammatory activities, respectively. The flavonoids and phenolic acids in Phyllanthus niruri contribute to its antioxidant and antimicrobial effects. Kaempferol has been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, which are essential for the plant's therapeutic benefits.",
