    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Phyllanthus niruri are tincture which is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant made by mixing it with a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to enhance its bioavailability and shelf life. Infusion is a method of extracting the bioactive compounds from the plant by steeping it in hot water for a period of time to release the active ingredients. Tea is prepared by steeping the dried leaves of Phyllanthus niruri in hot water to produce a flavonoid-rich beverage. Capsule is a convenient form of supplementing with the plant's bioactive compounds by encapsulating them in a gelatin or vegetarian shell to ensure bioavailability and convenience. Decoction involves boiling the dried roots or stems of the plant in water to release the active compounds which is useful for treating digestive issues and other health concerns.",
