    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Phyllanthus niruri improperly are due to its potential interactions with medications, specifically blood thinners, diabetes medications and certain antidepressants, which can lead to excessive bleeding, blood sugar fluctuations and increased serotonin levels. Additionally, improper use of Phyllanthus niruri may trigger allergic reactions, such as hives, itching, and difficulty breathing, in individuals with pre-existing allergies. Ingestion of excessive amounts of Phyllanthus niruri can cause nausea, vomiting and diarrhea, due to its emetic properties and ability to alter gut motility. Furthermore, prolonged or excessive use of Phyllanthus niruri has been linked to liver damage and dysfunction, particularly in individuals with pre-existing liver conditions, due to its potential hepatotoxic effects. These side effects can be attributed to the plant's complex chemical composition, which includes flavonoids, alkaloids, and terpenoids, that can interact with various biological pathways and systems."
